# ENVS 193DS Homework 3

## General Information 

This repo looks at an example of a Pearson's correlation test ($r$) using data 
on ocean temperature impact on giant kelp (*Macrocystis pyrifera*) elongation 
rates. 

Additionally this repo looks updates visualizations and begins outlining affective 
visualization for my personal data: “Mechanisms of severe dieback and mortality in a classically
drought-tolerant shrubland species (*Arctostaphylos glauca*)” *American Journal of Botany*.

